Charter for Regional or Minority Languages” of the Council of Europe now applies in 25 states. The articles in this volume examine the basic concept and the language planning measures of the treaty from the linguistic and legal perspectives. A large number of concrete case studies are used to investigate whether the Charter is adequate to current European situations of multilingualism and whether it provides convincing solutions to situations of linguistic conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLinguistic minoritiesxLegal status, laws, etc.zEurope. 4aEthnische Minderheit. 4aGesetzgebung. 4aSprachplanung. 4aSprachpolitik. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Cultural Policy.2bisacsh  aLanguage politics.  aethnic minority.  alanguage planning.  alegislation.1 aBartholomä, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFischer, Roswitha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHofmann, Mahulena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLebsanft, Franz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLebsanft, Franz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNuolijärvi, Pirkko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPirazzini, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTacke, Felix, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aViaut, Alain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWicherkiewicz, Tomasz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWingender, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWingender, Monika, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWiśniewiecka-Brückner, Katarzyna,